sentences: She moved to New York to marry jazz bassist Gary Peacock in 1960.

She performed with the Bley-Peacock Synthesizer Show at New York's Town Hall in November 1969 and the next month at Philharmonic Hall which she promoted with late-night TV ads and an appearance on The Johnny Carson Show.
Her official debut solo album, I'm the One (RCA Victor), was released in 1972.
The album An Acrobat's Heart (ECM, 2000) took two years to compose and arrange, and broke her twelve-year hiatus from recording.

She is self-taught except for her time as a student at The Juilliard School in the early 1970s.
During the 1970s and '80s, she worked with Karlheinz Stockhausen, Allan Holdsworth, Evan Parker, Brian Eno, Bill Bruford, Mike Garson, Mick Ronson before moving back to the U.S.
She is a pioneer in electronic music who combined her voice with one of the first Moog synthesizers in the late 1960s.
During the early 1960s, she was an associate and guest of Timothy Leary.
Annette Peacock was writing music by the time she was four years old.

She performed with the Bley-Peacock Synthesizer Show at New York's Town Hall in November 1969 and the next month at Philharmonic Hall which she promoted with late-night TV ads and an appearance on The Johnny Carson Show.
